Ada Web Application

Ada Web Application is a framework to build a Web Application in Ada 2005.

It integrates the following projects:

 - ASF      (http://code.google.com/p/ada-asf)
 - ADO      (http://code.google.com/p/ada-ado)
 - Ada Util (http://code.google.com/p/ada-util)
 - Ada EL   (http://code.google.com/p/ada-el)
 - Dynamo   (http://code.google.com/p/ada-gen)

 These projects are provided as tarball in 'distrib' directory.
 These projects are distributed under the Apache License 2.0.

It relies on the following external projects:

 - AWS      (http://libre.adacore.com/libre/tools/aws/)
 - XMLAda   (http://libre.adacore.com/libre/tools/xmlada/)
 - AUnit    (http://libre.adacore.com/libre/tools/aunit/)

 These projects are provided as tarball in 'external' directory.
 They are distributed under different licenses (GNU GPL).
 They are not compiled.


Extract the sources and configure by using:

   ./configure


If you wan to build AWS, XMLAda or AUnit, you can configure with:


   ./configure --enable-aunit --enable-xmlada --enable-aws


Then, build the packages by using:

   make


Documentation

   The Ada Web Application sources as well as a wiki documentation is provided on:

   http://code.google.com/p/ada-awa/


